        "\n",
        "\n",
        "The sternoclavicular joint is a synovial saddle joint\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Muscles\n",
        "\n",
        "# Connective tissue\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Joint Structure\n",
        "\n",
        "Since the SCJ is a saddle joint, both the distal and proximal joint surfaces have concave and convex facets.\n",
        "\n",
        "- Frontal plane: \n",
        "    - Convex clavicle on Concave sternum\n",
        "    - Superior roll and inferior slide\n",
        "- Transverse plane:\n",
        "    - Concave clavicle on convex sternum \n",
        "    - Anterior roll and slide\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "- 6&deg; upward slope\n",
        "- Posterior to the frontal plane 20 deg\n",
        "\n",
        "# Kinematics\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "The sternoclavicular joint has 3 degrees of freedom:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Frontal plane**: [Elevation](#elevation) & [Depression](#depression)\n",
        "1. **Transverse plane**: [Protraction](#protraction) & [Retraction](#retraction)\n",
        "1. **Sagittal plane**: [Anterior rotation](#anterior-rotation) and [Posterior rotation](#posterior-rotation)\n",
        "\n",
        "These movements combine to place the scapula in a position to optimally accept the head of the humerus @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "As a result, all of the functional movements at the [glenohumeral joint]({{< var ref-glenohumeral-joint.path >}}) involve SCJ movement.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## Elevation {#elevation}\n",
        "\n",
        "- The SCJ has 35-45&deg; of elevation @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "    - Endrange elevation is limited by the [costoclavicular ligament]({{< var ref-costoclavicular-ligament.path >}}).\n",
        "\n",
        "In open kinetic chain, elevation involves the movement of the convex clavicle on the concave sternum.\n",
        "As a result, the convex clavicle rolls *superiorly* and slides inferiorly @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "\n",
        "In closed chain, the concave sternum rolls superiorly and slides superiorly on the convex clavicle.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Depression {#depression}\n",
        "\n",
        "- The SCJ has ~10&deg; of depression from neutral @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "    - Endrange depression stretches the i[nterclavicular ligament]({{< var ref-interclavicular-ligament.path >}}) and the superior portion of the capsular ligaments @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "- In Open kinetic chain, the convex clavicle rolls *inferiorly* and slides *superiorly* on the concave sternum @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "- In closed chain, the concave sternum rolls and slides *inferiorly* on the convex clavicle.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## Protraction {#protraction}\n",
        "\n",
        "- Protraction and retraction both have ~15-30&deg; from neutral @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "- This movement occurs in the transverse or horizontal plane around the vertical axis of rotation @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "\n",
        "- During open kinetic chain protraction, the concave clavicle rolls and slides anteriorly on the convex sternum @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "- Closed chain protraction involves the convex sternum rolling anteriorly and sliding posteriorly.\n",
        "\n",
        "This movement is limited by:\n",
        "\n",
        "- [Posterior bundle of the costoclavicular ligament]({{< var ref-costoclavicular-ligament.path >}})\n",
        "- Posterior capsular ligament of the SC joint @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017\n",
        "- Scapular retractor muscles @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017\n",
        "    - [Rhomboid major]({{< var ref-rhomboid-major.path >}})\n",
        "    - [Rhomboid minor]({{< var ref-rhomboid-minor.path >}})\n",
        "    - [Middle trapezius]({{< var ref-middle-trapezius.path >}})\n",
        "\n",
        "## Retraction {#retraction}\n",
        "\n",
        "- This movement occurs in the transverse or horizontal plane around the vertical axis of rotation @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "- Protraction and retraction both have ~15-30&deg; from neutral @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "    - Endrange retraction stretches the [*anterior bundles* of the costoclavicular ligament]({{< var ref-costoclavicular-ligament.path >}}) and the anterior capsular ligaments @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "- During open kinetic chain retraction, the concave clavicle rolls and slides *posteriorly* on the convex sternum @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "- Closed chain retraction involves the convex sternum *posteriorly* rolling and *anteriorly* sliding on the concave clavicle.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Anterior rotation {#anterior-rotation}\n",
        "\n",
        "- Refers to rotation around the longitudinal axis @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## Posterior rotation {#posterior-rotation}\n",
        "\n",
        "- Refers to rotation around the longitudinal axis @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "- The SCJ can perform ~20-35&deg; of posterior rotation @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "- This motion involves arthrokinematic spin and does not follow the convex-concave rule @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "- Posterior rotation is important in [posterior tilt of the scapulothoraic joint]({{< var ref-scapulothoracic-joint.posterior-tilt >}}).\n",
        "\n",
        "This motion is important during full flexion and abduction of the shoulder @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "\n",
        "# Functional movements\n",
        "\n",
        "The clavicle and therefore the SCJ requires rotation in all 3 degrees of freedom when raising the arm overhead @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017.\n",
        "\n",
        "# Palpation {#palpation}\n",
        "\n",
        "To palpate the sternoclavicular joint:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Locate the *suprasternal notch*, which can be found on the superior aspect of the manubrium @finandoTriggerPointTherapy2005.\n",
        "- Move laterally from the *suprasternal notch* to the sternoclavicular joint @finandoTriggerPointTherapy2005.\n",
        "- Alternating elevation and depression of the shoulder while palpating the joint will help you to clearly distinguish between the [manubrium]({{< var ref-sternum-bone.manubrium >}}) and the [clavicle]({{< var ref-clavicle-bone.path >}}) @finandoTriggerPointTherapy2005.\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-note}\n",
        "At the sternoclavicular joint, the [clavicle]({{< var ref-clavicle-bone.path >}}) is raised slightly above the manubrium at the articulation @finandoTriggerPointTherapy2005.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Stabilization\n",
        "\n",
        "Tissues that stabilize the SCJ:\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.columns}\n",
        "::: {.column}\n",
        "### Passive Stabilizers\n",
        "\n",
        "- Anterior sternoclavicular joint ligament @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017\n",
        "- Posterior sternoclavicular joint ligament @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017\n",
        "- Interclavicular ligament @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017\n",
        "- Costoclavicular ligament @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017\n",
        "- Articular disc @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017\n",
        "\n",
        ":::\n",
        "::: {.column}\n",
        "### Active Stabilizers\n",
        "\n",
        "- [Subclavius]({{< var ref-subclavius.path >}}) [@duttonDuttonOrthopaedicExamination2020; @gilroyAtlasAnatomy2020; @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017]\n",
        "- [Sternocleidomastoid]({{< var ref-sternocleidomastoid.path >}}) @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017\n",
        "- [Sternothyroid]({{< var ref-sternothyroid.path >}}) @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017\n",
        "- [Sternohyoid]({{< var ref-sternohyoid.path >}}) @neumannKinesiologyMusculoskeletalSystem2017\n",
        "\n",
        ":::\n",
        ":::\n"
      ],
